    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="251"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d251">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2487a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Commission of Neutrals (<persName
                            corresp="#p_WF1" type="from">White</persName>) to the President of the
                        Council of the League of Nations (<persName corresp="#p_DVE1" type="to">De
                            Valera</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-05">November 5,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Commission of Neutrals takes pleasure advising you Bolivia and Paraguay have
                    accepted Commission’s suggestion to open direct negotiations under auspices of
                    Neutral Commission for termination of hostilities and to arrange for arbitral
                    settlement of dispute. These negotiations have been duly opened and are
                    proceeding normally.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis White</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
